I setup a project with micronaut to handle an SQSEvent. I got a lot of problems for read the SQS event in my function.&lt;br&gt;
I used the https://micronaut.io/launch to generate my project with the next params:&lt;br&gt;
Application Type: Function Application for Serverless&lt;br&gt;
Micronaut Version: 3.9.3&lt;br&gt;
Java Version: 17&lt;br&gt;
Build Tool: Gradle&lt;br&gt;
Test Framework: JUnit&lt;br&gt;
Additional features: aws-lambda, graalvm&lt;br&gt;
https://i.stack.imgur.com/MNoYc.png&lt;br&gt;

**build.gradle**

    dependencies {
    annotationProcessor(&quot;io.micronaut:micronaut-http-validation&quot;)

    implementation(&quot;com.amazonaws:aws-lambda-java-events:3.11.2&quot;)
    implementation(&quot;io.micronaut:micronaut-http-client&quot;)
    implementation(&quot;io.micronaut:micronaut-jackson-databind&quot;)
    implementation(&quot;io.micronaut.aws:micronaut-function-aws&quot;)
    implementation(&quot;io.micronaut.aws:micronaut-function-aws-custom-runtime&quot;)
    implementation(&quot;jakarta.annotation:jakarta.annotation-api&quot;)
    implementation(&quot;io.micronaut.data:micronaut-data-jdbc&quot;)

    compileOnly(&quot;org.graalvm.nativeimage:svm&quot;)
    runtimeOnly(&quot;ch.qos.logback:logback-classic&quot;)
}
&lt;br&gt;
**FunctionLambdaRuntime.java**

    public class FunctionLambdaRuntime extends AbstractMicronautLambdaRuntime&lt;SQSEvent, SQSBatchResponse, SQSEvent, SQSBatchResponse&gt;{
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try {
            new FunctionLambdaRuntime().run(args);

        } catch (MalformedURLException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

    @Override
    @Nullable
    protected RequestHandler&lt;SQSEvent, SQSBatchResponse&gt; createRequestHandler(String... args) {
        return new FunctionRequestHandler();
    }
}
&lt;br&gt;
**FunctionRequestHandler.java**&lt;br&gt;
Very important to add the Introspected annotation to the SQS necessary classes for the request and response!! You&#39;ll get a serialization error if you dont do this!

    @Introspected(classes = {SQSEvent.class, SQSEvent.SQSMessage.class, SQSBatchResponse.class, SQSEvent.MessageAttribute.class, SQSBatchResponse.BatchItemFailure.class})
    public class FunctionRequestHandler extends MicronautRequestHandler&lt;SQSEvent, SQSBatchResponse&gt; {
    @Inject
    ObjectMapper objectMapper;

    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(FunctionRequestHandler.class);

    @Override
    public SQSBatchResponse execute(SQSEvent input) {
        final List&lt;SQSBatchResponse.BatchItemFailure&gt; batchItemFailures = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
        final SQSBatchResponse response = new SQSBatchResponse(batchItemFailures);
        logger.info(&quot;SQS input: {}&quot;, input.toString());
        if(input == null){
            logger.error(&quot;SQSEvent input is null&quot;);
            return response;
        }
        logger.info(&quot;records {}&quot;, input.getRecords());

        for (SQSEvent.SQSMessage message : input.getRecords()) {
            try {
                MessagePaymentNotificationDto notification = this.objectMapper.readValue(message.getBody(), MessagePaymentNotificationDto.class);
                logger.info(notification.toString());
            } catch (Exception e) {
                batchItemFailures.add(new SQSBatchResponse.BatchItemFailure(message.getMessageId()));
            }

        }
        return response;
    }
}
&lt;br&gt;
Build the native image: *./gradlew buildNativeLambda -Pmicronaut.runtime=lambda* &lt;br&gt;
Upload the zip to your lambda function and configure com.example.eventHandlers.FunctionRequestHandler as handler.&lt;br&gt;
In the **Test** tab of your lambda function go to the **Template** section and search for SQS and select it, it will configure a test json with the structure of an SQSEvent:&lt;br&gt;
**Important:** When slected the SQS template the **&quot;records&quot;** attribute will be displayed as **&quot;Records&quot;**, change it to lowercase before send the test

