 2. If you are using new instance and start it from your Test class (for example `@Before`) :
````
import static com.github.tomakehurst.wiremock.core.WireMockConfiguration.options;

...

public class Test {

    WireMockServer wm;

    @BeforeEach
    void setUp() {
        wm = new WireMockServer(options().port(8888));
        wm.start();
    }

    @Test
    void test() {
        wm.stubFor(...);
    }
}
````
 3. With static configuration of default instance (not using new instance in your test) :
````
WireMock.configureFor(8888);
````
# For Kotlin users

If you are using kotlin you can add actual wiremock instance to `stubFor` and `verify` calls like `wm.stubFor()` and configure the port like in option 3 of this answer.

