&gt; _&quot;... When I am trying to print st.peek() I got output: Example$pair@4617c264&quot;_

This is just a naming scheme used by Java, which will be returned when trying to convert an _Object_ to a _String_.

The _[System#out#println](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/20/docs/api/java.base/java/io/PrintStream.html#println(java.lang.Object))_ method is taking an _Object_ as a parameter, not a _String_.

Here is the source, for _println_.  
_[GitHub &amp;ndash; jdk/src/java.base/share/classes/java/io/PrintStream.java](https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/blob/master/src/java.base/share/classes/java/io/PrintStream.java#L1186)_.

Which is using the following, more-or-less&amp;mdash;where _x_ is of type, _Object_.

```java
String s = String.valueOf(x);
```

An _Object_ can provide a _String_ resolution by overriding the inherited _[Object#toString](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/20/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/Object.html#toString())_ method.

Here is the source, for _Object#toString_.  
_[GitHub &amp;ndash; jdk/src/java.base/share/classes/java/lang/Object.java](https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/blob/master/src/java.base/share/classes/java/lang/Object.java#L265)_.

